jobs.description:
I lead a team of M&A and corporate transactional lawyers, focused on the structuring and commercialisation of early stage intellectual property, largely in the biomedical, life sciences, engineering and education spaces. This innovative work involves M&A transactions, capital raising via VC funds for start-up and spin-out entities, negotiating licensing arrangements and acting as the leading lawyer on broader initiatives, including:

- the creation of a large ($200M+) IP specific investment fund involving the G08 Universities, the largest fund of its kind in Australia (see press release at https://www.ipgroupplc.com/media/ip-group-news/2017/2017-05-30);

- the establishment BioCurate Pty Ltd, an innovative $80M "venture catalyst" JV between the University of Melbourne and Monash University with funding from State Government to focused on translating early stage life-sciences IP from benchtop to the point where it represents an investable proposition to third parties (further details at https://www.afr.com/news/biocurate-plots-team-oz-approach-20161031-gsehls);

leading the negotiation of landmark education curriculum licensing arrangements between the University and the Ministry of Education of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to modernise their national education curriculum across 36,000 schools (further details at http://newsroom.melbourne.edu/news/saudi-arabia-chooses-melbourne-experts-transform-education).

Counselcorp provides high quality commercial legal, corporate advisory and communication services to businesses and individuals. We specialise in providing high quality advice and end-to-end transactional services for:

• Mergers and Acquisitions;
• Capital Markets;
• Property Law;
• Health, Biomedical and Pharmaceutical Law;
• Competition/Trade Practices Law;
• Company Secretarial Services;
• General Contract Law.

The Ascent Group (Australia) manufactures, sells and distributes pharmaceuticals, dermatology and skin-care products, hospital products and a range of other "over the counter" health related products throughout Australia and South-East Asia. 

Management of Ascent's Legal Department has encompassed a broad spectrum of corporate/commercial legal work, including:

• Negotiation and settlement of licence, supply and distribution arrangements for the supply of generic pharmaceuticals to Australian and South-East Asian territories;
• Management of compliance with Australian competition and consumer law;
• Management of general corporate governance;
• Risk management;
• IP Portfolio management; 
• Liaison with the TGA and overseas government health authorities; and
• Management of M&A and commercial transactions.

During my time at Max Biocare, my activities encompassed:

- the review of pharmacological research concerning complementary medicines and their active ingredients;

- Designing complementary medicines and presenting their pharmacological profiles at local and international health conferences (key speaker at alternative hormone replacement conference in Hue, Vietnam in November 2008);

- Arranging for approval of complementary medicines by the TGA;

- Writing scientific articles for publication on website and journals;

- Designing clinical trials to test the efficacy of complementary medications; and

- Handling customer queries.

This specialist role works with People Leaders and Employees to address/resolve employee relations issues and manage business risk in line withpolicies, applicable industrial instruments and our regulatory obligations.
The Case Consultant manages a portfolio of employee relations cases including:
 Employee grievances and complaints;
 Misconduct;
 Formal performance management;
 Injury, illness and absence (where employment is affected); and
 Whistleblower complaints.

I joined Schiavello Group, one of Australia's largest privately owned companies, as the National Business Relationship Manager. This allowed me to build on my extensive management experience while developing additional skills  associated with the growth and development of the company's operations across a broad range of industries. My key responsibilities included;

     Developing an in depth understanding of the business's interrelated activities in order to identify efficiency improvements and increase customer service standards;
     Fostering strong working relationships with a network of internal and external stakeholders in order to execute agreements with clients across numerous industries;
     Liaising with the client in order to understand their requirements and develop turnkey solutions covering all aspects of project management, construction and fit out.
